Fix Author HQ load/clicks; quiet two Helmet console warnings

Author HQ (pre-existing bugs, surfaced post-split):
- /api/activity returns { entries }, not { events } — loadHQ read .events, so
  `events` became the wrapper object and events.slice() threw → the
  "Could not load HQ data" error. Now reads entries (tolerates array/legacy).
- HQ queried /api/projects (404s) instead of /api/projects/list, and ?limit
  instead of ?count — so HQ stats were always empty. Fixed.
- Active-project cards + the empty-state "Projects" link used inline onclick
  referencing module-scoped functions (no-ops) — replaced with addEventListener
  (switchPanel + openProjectDetail).

Console noise (Helmet headers, gateway/src/index.ts):
- Disable crossOriginOpenerPolicy + originAgentCluster. The server runs plain
  HTTP on the LAN (no TLS by design), so the browser ignores COOP and just logs
  a warning, and Origin-Agent-Cluster only logs a "could not be origin-keyed"
  warning for this single-origin app. Neither adds value here; disabling clears
  the dev console. (The bulk of the console errors are the user's LastPass
  extension — not BookClaw.)

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean; npm test green (34 unit + API + smoke).
